video_description: The unfiltered, raw reaction of finding out the gender of our baby 🤭!! In honor of finding out the gender of our baby girl a week ago, I thought I’d be open about how I trult felt in that moment.  While I’m so excited to do all the cute, girly things with my baby and having a mini bestie… this was my initial reaction. And its not that I was disappointed or didnt want her. I was overfilled with so many emotions, and essentially so many fears/worries.  In my own life, I had just been through so much trauma and heart ache. The thought of having a girl, in an unplanned pregnancy, with what feels like no time to prepare, scared the heck out of me. I couldnt help but think I wasnt ready to raise a girl or not where I want to be yet to have essentially a little me… looking up to me. I just had such an overwhelming fear of my daughter experiencing the things I have gone through and wanting to protect her.  But I dont believe any of that, and in fact, I rebuke it. I am excited for this journey, and also do see how motherhood will be another journey of healing parts of me I didnt know still needed it.  Also, I am so grateful for my partner. It’s so important to know and choose the person you want to do life with. Im grateful to have a man that will sit with me, let me feel, comfort me, and encourage me. Off camera, he said, “I think youll be a much greater girl mom than you think”. I love that I get to do this with him 💕  #pregnancy #genderreveal #unfiltered #motherhoodjourney #couple #christian #relationships #faith #healingjourney
